{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbf663318-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12204"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"12204"},"text":"§ 12204.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Regulations by Architectural and Transportation Barriers Compliance Board","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbf663319-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12204/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Issuance of guidelines","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than 9 months after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-07-26"},"text":"July 26, 1990","children":[],"tail":", the Architectural and Transportation Barriers Compliance Board shall issue minimum guidelines that shall supplement the existing Minimum Guidelines and Requirements for Accessible Design for purposes of subchapters II and III of this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbf66331a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12204/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Contents of guidelines","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The supplemental guidelines issued under subsection (a) shall establish additional requirements, consistent with this chapter, to ensure that buildings, facilities, rail passenger cars, and vehicles are accessible, in terms of architecture and design, transportation, and communication, to individuals with disabilities.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbf66331b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12204/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Qualified historic properties","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf66331c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12204/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The supplemental guidelines issued under subsection (a) shall include procedures and requirements for alterations that will threaten or destroy the historic significance of qualified historic buildings and facilities as defined in 4.1.7(1)(a) of the Uniform Federal Accessibility Standards.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf66331d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12204/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Sites eligible for listing in National Register","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"With respect to alterations of buildings or facilities that are eligible for listing in the National Register of Historic Places under division A of subtitle III of title 54, the guidelines described in paragraph (1) shall, at a minimum, maintain the procedures and requirements established in 4.1.7(1) and (2) of the Uniform Federal Accessibility Standards.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf66331e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12204/c/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Other sites","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"With respect to alterations of buildings or facilities designated as historic under State or local law, the guidelines described in paragraph (1) shall establish procedures equivalent to those established by 4.1.7(1)(b) and (c) of the Uniform Federal Accessibility Standards, and shall require, at a minimum, compliance with the requirements established in 4.1.7(2) of such standards.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbf66331f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/336/tV/s504"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–336, title V, § 504","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-07-26"},"text":"July 26, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/370"},"text":"104 Stat. 370","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/287/s5/k/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–287, § 5(k)(5)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/3270"},"text":"128 Stat. 3270","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbf663320-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbf663321-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idbf663322-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in subsecs. (a) and (b), was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/336"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–336","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-07-26"},"text":"July 26, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/327"},"text":"104 Stat. 327","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s12101"},"text":"section 12101 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idbf663323-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2014—Subsec. (c)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/287"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–287","children":[],"tail":" substituted “division A of subtitle III of title 54” for “the National Historic Preservation Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s470"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 470","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
